setDueDate

public TaskList setDueDate(String timeline,
                           String listID,
                           String seriesID,
                           String taskID,
                           String due,
                           String hasDueTime,
                           String parse)
                    throws MilkException
Sets the due date for a task. (rtm.tasks.setDueDate)

Parameters:
timeline - The timeline to be associated with this method call.
listID - The ID of the list containing the task.
seriesID - The ID of the series containing the task.
taskID - The ID of the task.
due - The due date for a task, in ISO 8601 format. 'due' is always parsed in the user's timezone (as found in rtm.settings.getList). An empty value will unset any due date.
hasDueTime - Specifies whether the due date has a due time (1 or 0). An empty value defaults to 0 (no due time).
parse - Specifies whether to parse 'due' as per rtm.time.parse (1 or 0). An empty value defaults to 0 (do not parse).
Returns:
A TaskList containing the Taskseries and task.
Throws:
MilkException
